{{Quote|I've brought you some bloodsoup.|Githany, to Darth Bane|<ref name="jvs">[[Jedi vs. Sith 2|''Jedi vs. Sith'' 2]]</ref>}}
'''Bloodsoup''' was a type of [[Soup/Legends|soup]] that the [[Sith (species)/Legends|Sith species]] traditionally drank. Some historians speculated that the Sith began consuming it after encountering the [[Anzat (species)|Anzati]].<ref name="tsd">{{Hyperspace|url=hyperspace/member/insideronline/88/indexp2.html|text=''Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties''|int=Evil Never Dies: The Sith Dynasties}}</ref> Around [[28,000 BBY]], [[Adas]] drank the bloodsoup of his enemies to honor their [[Death/Legends|deaths]].<ref name="BoS">''[[Book of Sith: Secrets from the Dark Side]]''</ref>

During the [[Ruusan campaign]] of the [[New Sith Wars]], [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane]] drank bloodsoup. [[Githany]] offered Bane a bowl after he returned from her attempt to poison him.<ref name="jvs" /><ref name="pod">''[[Darth Bane: Path of Destruction]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The [[Soup/Legends|soup]] that [[Githany]] offered [[Darth Bane/Legends|Darth Bane]] isn't identified as bloodsoup in ''[[Darth Bane: Path of Destruction]]''.<ref name="pod" />

